This paper is about personalized news recommendation, which is a subfield of information retrieval (cs.IR) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed approach involves using neural networks to learn informative representations of news and users, which is a common topic in natural language processing (cs.CL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the approach also involves using attention mechanisms, which is a popular technique in both machine learning and information retrieval, and can be categorized under cs.SI (social and information networks).
